        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "And my law as the apple of thine eye — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "With all possible care and diligence, as men guard that most noble and necessary, and therefore highly-esteemed and beloved part of the body from all danger, yea, even from the least mote. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Bind them upon thy fingers — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "As a ring which is put upon them, and is continually in a man’s eye. Constantly remember and meditate upon them. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Write them, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "&c. — Fix them in thy mind and affection: see on ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "Proverbs 3:3",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Say unto wisdom, Thou art my sister — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "The name of ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "sister ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "is a name of friendship, often used between the husband and wife, and denotes the chaste love which he should have to wisdom. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Call understanding thy kinswoman — ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "The LXX. render it, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "greekheb",
        "text": "την δε φρονησιν γνωριμον περιποιησαι σεαυτω",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ", ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "Acquire to thyself prudence for an acquaintance; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "while other foolish young men seek wanton mistresses, whom they frequently call ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "sisters, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "or ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "ital",
        "text": "kinswomen, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "let wisdom be thy mistress; acquaint and delight thyself with her. Say to her, Thou art my sister, my spouse, my beloved: let her have the command of thy heart, and the conduct of thy life.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "p",
