    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "Keep my commandments and live,.... Not the commandments of the law only, but the commandments of Christ; and even the doctrines of Christ are so called, as faith in him, and love to the saints, ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "1 John 3:23",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "; which is the way to live comfortably, peaceably, pleasantly, and honourably; ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "and my law as the apple of thine eye; the doctrine of Christ, the law of the Lord, that goes out of Zion; which should be as dear to men as the apple of their eye, and as carefully preserved, that the least injury is not done to it; it should be kept inviolate. ",
