            "text": "Proverbs 7:1",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": " another distich; but it here disturbs the connection. Regarding צפן, vid., at ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Proverbs 2:1",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "",
            "text": "; אתּך refers, as there, to the sphere of one's own character, and that subjectively. Regarding the imper. וחיה, which must here be translated according to its sense as a conclusion, because it comes in between the objects governed by שׁמר, vid., at ",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
            "class": "verse-link",
            "text": "Proverbs 4:4",
            "children": []
          },
          {
            "element": "span",
